Package: Fonology
Type: Package
Title: Phonological Analysis in R
Version: 1.1.1
Authors@R: person(given = c("Guilherme", "D."), family = "Garcia",
                  role = c("aut", "cre", "cph"),
                  email = "guilherme.garcia@lli.ulaval.ca",
                  comment = c(
                              ORCID = "0000-0003-1412-3856")) 
Maintainer: Guilherme D. Garcia <guilherme.garcia@lli.ulaval.ca>
Description: A collection of tools for phonological analysis, with primary support for Portuguese, Spanish, French, and Italian, plus CMU-backed English transcription with user-correctable overrides and heuristic fallback for out-of-vocabulary forms. Functions include grapheme-to-phoneme conversion with syllabification and stress assignment, sonority dispersion calculation, minimal matrices for natural classes given a set of features, maxent models, and more.
